<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A Yeoman is distributing coffees when McCoy enters</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>DESALLE:  All clear ahead, Captain. The sensors indicate zero register.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>KIRK:  Forward readings, Mister Spock.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Gravimetric readings, no significant change, zero space density.</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KIRK:  Ahead warp factor three, Mister Sulu. Colony Beta Six wants their supplies. Let's get across this void in a hurry.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Void, star desert. The word conjures up pictures of dunes, oases, mirages.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>KIRK:  Sunlight, palm trees. We're nine hundred light years from that kind of desert, Bones.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>SPOCK:  The precise meaning of the word desert is a waterless, barren wasteland. I fail to understand your romantic nostalgia for such a place.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>MCCOY:  That doesn't surprise me, Mister Spock. I can't imagine a mirage ever disturbing those mathematically perfect brain waves of yours.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Thank you, Doctor McCoy. Moving on schedule into quadrant nine oh four. Beta Six is eight days distant.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>KIRK:  Something, Mister Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Unusual, Captain. I'm now getting a sizable space-displacement reading.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>KIRK:  Can you verify that, Navigator?</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>DESALLE:  No, sir. Forward sweeps are negative. Wait. Verified, sir. We must be in some sort of light warp or we'd have picked it up earlier.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>KIRK:  Put it on visual.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A purple globe appears on the viewscreen</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>DESALLE:  Iron-silica body, planet sized, magnitude one E. We'll be passing close.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Inconceivable this body has gone unnoted on all our records.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>KIRK:  And yet, here it is. No time to investigate. Science stations, gather data for computer banks. Uhura, notify the discovery on subspace radio.</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>UHURA:  Strong interference on subspace, Captain. The planet must be a natural radio source.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>KIRK:  Let's get out of its range. Veer forty degrees to starboard, Mister Sulu.</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>SULU:  Forty degrees.</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He reaches for the switch, and sways as if dizzy, then stands up and vanishes</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>KIRK:  Sulu!</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: He dashes to Sulu's station, then suddenly stops and disappears too</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>DESALLE:  Mister Spock, they're gone!</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Emergency! Full reverse power!</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Ship's log Stardate 2124.5. First Officer Spock reporting for Captain James Kirk. We are orbiting the lone unrecorded planet in the star desert. For four hours, we have made every possible instrument sweep, but Captain Kirk and Helmsman Sulu remain unaccounted for. I have placed the ship on red alert.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L29"><td><a href="#L29">29</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Enterprise is now orbiting a red planet with white whispy clouds</td></tr>

<tr id="L30"><td><a href="#L30">30</a></td><td>SCOTT:  We've searched again from stem to stern. If they're not down on that planet, they're nowhere.</td></tr>

<tr id="L31"><td><a href="#L31">31</a></td><td>DESALLE:  No sign of human life on the surface, sir. Unless the instruments aren't functioning.</td></tr>

<tr id="L32"><td><a href="#L32">32</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Function is normal. Continuous sensor sweeps. Lieutenant Uhura, have you checked all wave bands?</td></tr>

<tr id="L33"><td><a href="#L33">33</a></td><td>UHURA:  All of them, Mister Spock. No response.</td></tr>

<tr id="L34"><td><a href="#L34">34</a></td><td>DESALLE:  With due respect, sir. Request permission to transport to the surface immediately and carry out a search.</td></tr>

<tr id="L35"><td><a href="#L35">35</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I second DeSalle's request. What are we waiting for?</td></tr>

<tr id="L36"><td><a href="#L36">36</a></td><td>SPOCK:  The decision will be mine, Doctor. I have the responsibility for your safety. (to Sulu's replacement) Mister Jaeger, describe your geophysical findings for the surface below.</td></tr>

<tr id="L37"><td><a href="#L37">37</a></td><td>JAEGER:  No detectable soil or vegetation. Extremely hot, toxic atmosphere swept by tornadic storm. Continuous volcanic eruptions. Deadly to any lifeforms such as we know it without oxygen and life-support systems.</td></tr>

<tr id="L38"><td><a href="#L38">38</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Estimate survival time of two unprotected individuals down there.</td></tr>

<tr id="L39"><td><a href="#L39">39</a></td><td>JAEGER:  Not very long.</td></tr>

<tr id="L40"><td><a href="#L40">40</a></td><td>UHURA:  Mister Spock. Look.</td></tr>

<tr id="L41"><td><a href="#L41">41</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Words are appearing on the monitor above her head, in gothic script. Spock reads them out loud</td></tr>

<tr id="L42"><td><a href="#L42">42</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Greetings and felicitations. Hmm. Send this, Lieutenant. USS Enterprise to signaler on planet surface. Identify self.</td></tr>

<tr id="L43"><td><a href="#L43">43</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The reply comes up on the monitor</td></tr>

